
[1]histrionical

   HISTRION'ICAL, a. [L. histrionicus, from histrio, a buffoon, an actor,
   or stage player.]

   Pertaining to a buffoon or comedian, or to a pantomime, who represents
   events or characters by gestures and dancing; belonging to
   stage-playing; befitting a theater; theatrical.
